          "tz": 240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
          "email": "tappro@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-12-14 10:36:00.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2104 recovery: keep valid obd_stale_clients during recovery",
        "message": "LU-2104 recovery: keep valid obd_stale_clients during recovery\n\n- in class_fail_export() update obd_stale_clients counter if\n  recovery is in progress. That fixes endless recovery issues.\n- class_disconnect_stale_exports() should check exp_failed and\n  exclude such exports from being evicted once more.\n- set obd_no_conn flag in ofd_prepare() like mdt does.\n- remove check for obd_no_conn from check_for_clients(). That is\n  extra check as we don't allow any client to connect while\n  obd_no_conn is set\n\nSigned-off-by: Mikhail Pershin <tappro@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I439a1edd49a9c51f42df4c423d7c165468a3d38d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
